[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Examining native image workflows**\n\nI'm analyzing how a missing static metadata might cause a workflow failure in a native image. Previous test sources using Jackson introspection succeeded, so I'm curious why. The native image reflection config appears not to be generated properly. It seems that reachability metadata includes only VersionUtil. I wonder if the native tests even ran at all. The task may rely on JVM with instrumentation first and then move to native. I'll need to investigate the filtering rules, especially regarding shaded libraries.\n\n**Evaluating tracing agent filters**\n\nI’m wondering about how the native image tracing agent applies its filter rules. It seems that the evaluation might depend on the order, particularly if the first match is excluded. If the JSON filter states to exclude all classes but include shaded ones, I think the last match might take precedence. Therefore, test classes could end up excluded, but JUnit includes those classes. I might need to add metadata for our test to ensure successful field introspection during runtime.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0fa47d0df28626340169f2d34cf104819cb5c00acee496d03d\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp8tNZSE4I3DMwM5z5B6rxkO6vPYhBPLoBcAHYBc-24cdMQD8poQVgA6J_2QWfWhyF4eH93Vjsjuc_37XuPOqt_uzGg4ZOT-vs7a0K1bk40FZuNDYzE-LVpfiuFXO0qCG4fv7Od5fq8N_FoIGIj5IH6k36ga9go4MCyoGiQ9JBEqcLBx74_1rS4Pnuox_NbOiMxbpgoi_yODoP0aJAdsnhWkM3J1KLCwFeoEXnSo2kKptZirwyd-Fw8Fm5-lKJe6fx2NccWmFGb-RW2gqVqdjRLn-1LD0nw5Iy0TPXljQEVw0Xa5xzF1_EJdT-tVoeB3ggPe0f6bhillX-wA0Ygn8jRLXGUl24x_6onUBdn4um9Svc0nbTWD0lrj3YweubgLaXW-P_ZslAJXdFIH3osMBM2qRTsgkHMusvZZO-ZX89QMl0Pyzi7T6yv4QoRxxlYCb9mthyWDYWq5Glp_7vYRaCniA1Tt807aagWgvHKkTTX94Fqnu-zB-6FCW736VCYfTzoD1IF0jkL34MHutdAI2YlN2ta8qBdbFXAHf7u1wL9nNXbWIU4sFWQbnMVz-KZhgdcm0SA5_gBC7lzJxBK_JfaxieV2Ysvw3hGI2-KZRAMfqEWZBiS_sEThQZdZ_UKe-_ZBZ8HiRLSadqHlpStegA5